Still couldn't find the new issue of Jump today DDD:

And the the cosplay photos of canned pineapple made me cried. Amano really need to release Mukuro ASAP. 

Anyway, I wish that Amano would get serious. The current arc had been dragged on for too long. And Reborn! is neither a shojo or BL manga, so stop girlified/uke-fied(?) everyone :< Even though the new colour pictures are pretty, girly Hibari made me want to cry. 

Also, read the ending of Law of Ueki Plus today. I'm sad that this series ended so quickly. The last few chapters are too rushed. And I was hoping to see more characters from the first series appear at the end, but it didn't happen. I'm sad D:

The colour page of Target 150 is so pretty >///<

Run off to MK to buy Jump now.

EDIT: 
Returned from MK but couldn't find this issue of Jump. Why is airmail so slow? D: Anyway, I bought two 8059 doujishi by Nails though. So I'm happy :D

Hibari still haven't appear.

And the hand belongs to Kurokawa Hana. Does that mean that another extremely minor character will have an important role in Reborn again?!

Anyway, yay for more 8059 scene.

Once upon a time, I think that 8018 would be my biggest quirk. But now the only Reborn "pairing" that really annoy me is All27. Really, people, I know that Tsuna is a whiny coward that is kinda useless most of the time, but he is not completely weak and helpless. He doesn't need to be saved all the time. And he is not a blushy girl slut that seduce people OKAY. And if I read one more fanfic where 24 years old Tsuna is Byakuran's sex slave? I'm gonna kill a bitch. Anyway, no comment on the spoiler for Target 149. The only thing I look forward to now is the colour page in Target 150 >:

I hate HK weather. It was really hot the last few days. And today, it had been raining with occasional lightning and thunder the whole day. I was supposed to go out to MK to find stuff for cosplay this weekend, but er, there's no way that I'll go out with weather like that D:

Anyway, I spent the whole day playing with photoshop. And this is a pic from Target 145 that I coloured in:

As for Irie, I'm glad that he's not as uke as he is in the spoiler pic. Byakuran x Irie x Byakuran >///<

Cinepuri is like a bad fanfic. An extremely bad fanfic.

So... orientation for my course today and only 9 people turned up. But that's predictable since it's Friday night and the weather is bad. I'm just glad that the small thunder storm already ended when I left. I don't want to walk 15 minutes to the MTR station under thunder and lightning. Anyway the orientation itself was pretty useless since it just told us how to use the computers and the library. The only thing which I found interesting is that we can use Octopus Card for photocopying which is awesome. You really can use Octopus Card to do anything in HK. 

Also, I went to Sham Shui Po to buy the chain for the Org coat. But I can't find the beads I want, which is bad because I don't want to make them myself. Anyway, it's CW22 on Sun. I'm still wondering if I should cosplay or not. It's too hot and I'm too lazy to do anymore preparation.

And... I should go to sleep now since it's already 3:30am. - -'''

It had been awhile since the last time I wrote a non-private entry (i.e. apps for a certain RP) on LJ, so here are some not-reviews of movies and manga.

Movies I watched in August:

1. PoTC:DMC
I would had watch this movie in NZ if I knew that it would take forever to get on screen in HK. Q.Q Anyway, I think that this movie can be better. But it's still a good movie overall because Jack Sparrow is awesome. The sad thing is that I'm completely obsessed with KH so I kept on thinking that Sora would pop up to help. - -''' 
PS: Chinese subtitle sucks. 

2. Death Note
Surprisely, this movie is good. I originally dislike the the choice of actors is this movie: Firstly, the appearances of the actors look nothing like the original characters. (Light's actor is much of a pretty boy when L is not 'cute' enough). Secondly, I really hate L's actor performance in the NANA movie. 

However, after I watch the movie, the only thing I've in mind is that L is awesome! And he's definitely one of my favorite actors now. I mean... he's like the most perfect L ever! Even the best L cosplayer I saw can't get L's every little mannerism right, but he actually did it! And really... even if you don't like Death Note, you should watch this movie just for L 'cause even my mother like him. 

As for the movie itself, I know that some people actually think that it's too slow-paced. But I think that they balance it quite well with the funny moments. And the animation of Ryuk is great. As for the storyline itself, the change actually works better than I thought. The only bad thing about this movie is that... when Light's actor is sorta okay, I'm sure that they can find a better actor for this role. Oh, and Misa have the wrong hair colour but she really didn't appear much in this movie so I can't make any comments abour her.  


Manga I read last week:
1. Bleach ch239: Yay! Ishida ♥ 
2. DGM ch86: Yay! Kanda! ♥ ♥ ♥ 
3. FMA ch62: ♥ ♥ ♥ ♥ ♥
4. Ouran ch42: Standrad Ouran crack with slight tension. And I think that Kaoru is my favorite character in Ouran now.
5. Over Time ch 1-3: Sorta-new sport manga in Jump? A cross between HnG (ghost) and ES21 (sport)? The two main characters of this series kinda remind me of Hiruma and Sena... Anyway, he drawing style is okay for a shonen manga. The main character is cute; I'm sure that some fangirl would think that this series is slashable. But the first three chapters are too random. And a manga with such a bad beginning probably wouldn't be very good. I'm going to follow this manga for awhile though since it does look like it have potential.

<lj-cut text="Sleepy... but I'm still alive.">Umm... I'm sleepy but I should update my journal. And it's always fun to write when I'm not coherent. Anyway, HK is hot and wet and hot... <small>and that sounds so dirty - -''' </small> But the heat is good for my feet 'cause... yay! No more pain when I shower... <small>frostbitten foot really sucks...</small> Anyway... er... so the heat is actually kind of good and there's air conditioning everywhere anyway. But it's the humidity that kill me... can't breath properly... 80-90something% humdidity is EVIL! And... er... I don't really know what I'm talking about.

Anyway, I should start getting out instead of staying at home almost 24/7 even if the air conditioner and fast internet speed is shiny. And... I really should go to sleep before I faint. Hopefully, no thunder and lightning and rain so that I can sleep properly for once.

</lj-cut>

<lj-cut text="my feet hurt T.T">Today is a bad day. I don't think that my exam go very well (but I didn't study at all so...); I've post-exam anxiety (which actually serves me right); and my feet hurt. 

And something for me to read later:

http://www.podiatryvic.com.au/Public/Facts2.htm

"Chilblains:
With winter well on its way in Australia we have had some calls for a chilblain mix.
Chilblains sometimes called Pernio, are painful burning sensations in parts of the body previously frostbitten.
They are caused by exposure to cold, even slight cold. They are incredibly painful and create an intense itching that is at times difficult to satisfy.

Chilblains are difficult to treat and may recurr for years.

Frost bite can occur for a number of reasons including poor circulation due to arteriosclerosis, blood vessel spasms due to smoking or certain drugs or blood flow constriction due to tight socks and boots.

For chronic chilblains I suggest the internal mix for Blood Circulation for Extremities.
http://www.herbal-treatment.net/herbs_circulation_extremities.html

Externally I suggest the irritant oil which includes Linseed Oil, Tea Tree Oil, Rosemary Oil, Thyme Oil , Comfrey and Aloes along with the Bach Flowers Chestnut Bud and Aspen. Together this mix will reduce swelling, increase circulation and restore healthy skin cells.

Chilblains can be a treated from a nutritional point of view as well, by looking at your a balanced intake of Vit. A, D and Calcium. Cod Liver Oil , Dandelion tea and Fenugreek tea or sprouts are just some ways to address this problem. "




And, I think that the fact that I get frostbitten when I was studying about Antarctica, which include stuff about how to prevent frostbite, is kind of amusing... Or, at least it would be if my toes are not completely swollen or itch like hell right now. Q.Q

</lj-cut>

<lj-cut text="Boring RL stuff goes here.">


I got accepted by one of the uni I applied for a few months ago. Baptist U (HKBU) is not a particularly good university. But I think that the program I applied for isn't that bad, consider the fact that I only applied for it because a stupid BSc is so useless that I need a Master degree in order to find a decent job. (And I still don't understand why I did I choose a biology-related major at the first place since I suck at this subject. D: )  

Anyway, the program I got accepted for is a MSc in Environmental & Public Health Management. It is a one year full time program, so I would be able to obtain a "Master degree" in just one year (as long as I don't fail) instead of the usual 2 years, which is a good thing for me. Also, what I can learn in this degree should be useful in my future, especially since I decided to rule out any career which would involve a lot of lab works. But the fact that this degree is about "management" worries me because management equals commerce to me. And, I don't have any commerce sense at all so I'm not sure if I would be able to do well in this degree. 

Most importantly, I don't really know what to think about the fact that I'm going to leave NZ for real this time. But er... I think that I'm going to write about it sometime later because what I really think about NZ and HK is too complicated for my mind to process right now. 

</lj-cut>

I just finished watching Ouran episode 5. All I can say is that the manga is great but the anime is even better! The little details (like the arrow which appears in every episodes) make the anime even funnier. And, I just love how Honey keeps on appearing out of nowhere in this episode. But most importantly, Nekozawa finally appears! 

So, Ouran is definitely my top favourite anime right now; and I also love Princess Princess, Saiunkoku and Jyu Oh Sei. As for manga, the only series I'm still following now are FMA and BLEACH. But I think that the latest chapters of BLEACH are quite disappointing, and FMA is too slow. And... I almost forget that I'm still reading Tenipuri. I really don't know why I'm still following this series though... I just hope that the story would pick up itself now that Shitenhouji appears again. 

Anyway, I really should write something which is non anime or manga related in this journal. I should try to write something about my life tomorrow, since I'm going to watch the new episodes of Gintama and BLEACH now. 

EDIT: 
A reminder for myself: Play KH2 later tonight!

EDIT 2: Gintama episode 5 = love! This episode is full of crack, especially the part where Yamazaki (?) cosplay as Ryoma.

I'm sad that I won't be able to go to Wellington Armageddon this year. I really want to go there for the Firefly/ Serenity panel and the cosplay competition (even though I'm not entering). It's just that the 29th and 30th aren't convenient days for me and that traveling to Wellington is too expensive. <small>And I can't find anyone to go with me.</small> But at least River's actor is not coming, or I would feel even worse.... 

Anyway, I need to think of what to do with my BLEACH shinigami costume now since I'm not going to Armageddon. I want to be able to wear it at least once in NZ.
